  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail and dice your<strong> carrot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Heat a very large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion</strong> and<strong> diced carrot</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> white cup mushrooms</strong> and <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> to a<strong> food processor</strong> and pulse for 5 secs or until roughly blitzed</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, add the <strong>blitzed mushrooms</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> dried oregano</strong> to the pan and increase the heat to medium-high</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the mushrooms are beginning to soften</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in your<strong> soy sauce</strong> and <strong>Marmite</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan with your <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong>,<strong> drained lentils</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 12-15 min or until thickened to a bolognese-like consistency – this is your <strong>mushroom ragù</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the pasta for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine </strong>and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the linguine is cooking, chop your<strong> basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the mushroom ragù and gently stir together until the ragù begins to stick to the linguine - this is your <strong>rich</strong> <strong>mushroom ragù linguine</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2445Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>rich mushroom ragù linguine</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped basil</strong>,<strong> Italian hard cheese shavings</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
